ucdavis.name: ucdavis

revisions.description: New object for number of CPUs as counted by the agent
New objects for monitoring CPU Steal, Guest and Nice values
New 64-bit objects for monitoring large disk usage
Clarify behaviour of objects in the memory & systemStats groups (including updated versions of malnamed mem*Text objects). Define suitable TCs to describe error reporting/fix behaviour.
Added ssCpuRawSoftIRQ for Linux (2.6) and forgotten raw swap counters.
Added raw CPU and IO counters.
SMIv2 version converted from older MIB definitions.

ucdavis.description: This file defines the private UCD SNMP MIB extensions.

Float.name: Float
Float.description: A single precision floating-point number. The semantics and encoding are identical for type 'single' defined in IEEE Standard for Binary Floating-Point, ANSI/IEEE Std 754-1985. The value is restricted to the BER serialization of the following ASN.1 type: FLOATTYPE ::= [120] IMPLICIT FloatType (note: the value 120 is the sum of '30'h and '48'h) The BER serialization of the length for values of this type must use the definite length, short encoding form. For example, the BER serialization of value 123 of type FLOATTYPE is '9f780442f60000'h. (The tag is '9f78'h; the length is '04'h; and the value is '42f60000'h.) The BER serialization of value '9f780442f60000'h of data type Opaque is '44079f780442f60000'h. (The tag is '44'h; the length is '07'h; and the value is '9f780442f60000'h.

UCDErrorFix.name: UCDErrorFix
UCDErrorFix.description: Represents a 'push-button' object, to invoke a suitable configured action. Will always return 0 when read.

prTable.name: prTable
prTable.description: A table containing information on running programs/daemons configured for monitoring in the snmpd.conf file of the agent. Processes violating the number of running processes required by the agent's configuration file are flagged with numerical and textual errors.

prEntry.name: prEntry
prEntry.description: An entry containing a process and its statistics.

prIndex.name: prIndex
prIndex.description: Reference Index for each observed process.

prNames.name: prNames
prNames.description: The process name we're counting/checking on.

prMin.name: prMin
prMin.description: The minimum number of processes that should be running. An error flag is generated if the number of running processes is < the minimum.

prMax.name: prMax
prMax.description: The maximum number of processes that should be running. An error flag is generated if the number of running processes is > the maximum.

prCount.name: prCount
prCount.description: The number of current processes running with the name in question.

prErrorFlag.name: prErrorFlag
prErrorFlag.description: A Error flag to indicate trouble with a process. It goes to 1 if there is an error, 0 if no error.

prErrMessage.name: prErrMessage
prErrMessage.description: An error message describing the problem (if one exists).

prErrFix.name: prErrFix
prErrFix.description: Setting this to one will try to fix the problem if the agent has been configured with a script to call to attempt to fix problems automatically using remote snmp operations.

prErrFixCmd.name: prErrFixCmd
prErrFixCmd.description: The command that gets run when the prErrFix column is set to 1.

extTable.name: extTable
extTable.description: A table of extensible commands returning output and result codes. These commands are configured via the agent's snmpd.conf file.

extEntry.name: extEntry
extEntry.description: An entry containing an extensible script/program and its output.

extIndex.name: extIndex
extIndex.description: Reference Index for extensible scripts. Simply an integer row number.

extNames.name: extNames
extNames.description: A Short, one name description of the extensible command.

extCommand.name: extCommand
extCommand.description: The command line to be executed.

extResult.name: extResult
extResult.description: The result code (exit status) from the executed command.

extOutput.name: extOutput
extOutput.description: The first line of output of the executed command.

extErrFix.name: extErrFix
extErrFix.description: Setting this to one will try to fix the problem if the agent has been configured with a script to call to attempt to fix problems automatically using remote snmp operations.

extErrFixCmd.name: extErrFixCmd
extErrFixCmd.description: The command that gets run when the extErrFix column is set to 1.

memIndex.name: memIndex
memIndex.description: Bogus Index. This should always return the integer 0.

memErrorName.name: memErrorName
memErrorName.description: Bogus Name. This should always return the string 'swap'.

memTotalSwap.name: memTotalSwap
memTotalSwap.description: The total amount of swap space configured for this host.

memAvailSwap.name: memAvailSwap
memAvailSwap.description: The amount of swap space currently unused or available.

memTotalReal.name: memTotalReal
memTotalReal.description: The total amount of real/physical memory installed on this host.

memAvailReal.name: memAvailReal
memAvailReal.description: The amount of real/physical memory currently unused or available.

memTotalSwapTXT.name: memTotalSwapTXT
memTotalSwapTXT.description: The total amount of swap space or virtual memory allocated for text pages on this host. This object will not be implemented on hosts where the underlying operating system does not distinguish text pages from other uses of swap space or virtual memory.

memAvailSwapTXT.name: memAvailSwapTXT
memAvailSwapTXT.description: The amount of swap space or virtual memory currently being used by text pages on this host. This object will not be implemented on hosts where the underlying operating system does not distinguish text pages from other uses of swap space or virtual memory. Note that (despite the name), this value reports the amount used, rather than the amount free or available for use. For clarity, this object is being deprecated in favour of 'memUsedSwapTXT(16).

memTotalRealTXT.name: memTotalRealTXT
memTotalRealTXT.description: The total amount of real/physical memory allocated for text pages on this host. This object will not be implemented on hosts where the underlying operating system does not distinguish text pages from other uses of physical memory.

memAvailRealTXT.name: memAvailRealTXT
memAvailRealTXT.description: The amount of real/physical memory currently being used by text pages on this host. This object will not be implemented on hosts where the underlying operating system does not distinguish text pages from other uses of physical memory. Note that (despite the name), this value reports the amount used, rather than the amount free or available for use. For clarity, this object is being deprecated in favour of 'memUsedRealTXT(17).

memTotalFree.name: memTotalFree
memTotalFree.description: The total amount of memory free or available for use on this host. This value typically covers both real memory and swap space or virtual memory.

memMinimumSwap.name: memMinimumSwap
memMinimumSwap.description: The minimum amount of swap space expected to be kept free or available during normal operation of this host. If this value (as reported by 'memAvailSwap(4)') falls below the specified level, then 'memSwapError(100)' will be set to 1 and an error message made available via 'memSwapErrorMsg(101)'.

memShared.name: memShared
memShared.description: The total amount of real or virtual memory currently allocated for use as shared memory. This object will not be implemented on hosts where the underlying operating system does not explicitly identify memory as specifically reserved for this purpose.

memBuffer.name: memBuffer
memBuffer.description: The total amount of real or virtual memory currently allocated for use as memory buffers. This object will not be implemented on hosts where the underlying operating system does not explicitly identify memory as specifically reserved for this purpose.

memCached.name: memCached
memCached.description: The total amount of real or virtual memory currently allocated for use as cached memory. This object will not be implemented on hosts where the underlying operating system does not explicitly identify memory as specifically reserved for this purpose.

memUsedSwapTXT.name: memUsedSwapTXT
memUsedSwapTXT.description: The amount of swap space or virtual memory currently being used by text pages on this host. This object will not be implemented on hosts where the underlying operating system does not distinguish text pages from other uses of swap space or virtual memory.

memUsedRealTXT.name: memUsedRealTXT
memUsedRealTXT.description: The amount of real/physical memory currently being used by text pages on this host. This object will not be implemented on hosts where the underlying operating system does not distinguish text pages from other uses of physical memory.

memTotalSwapX.name: memTotalSwapX
memTotalSwapX.description: The total amount of swap space configured for this host.

memAvailSwapX.name: memAvailSwapX
memAvailSwapX.description: The amount of swap space currently unused or available.

memTotalRealX.name: memTotalRealX
memTotalRealX.description: The total amount of real/physical memory installed on this host.

memAvailRealX.name: memAvailRealX
memAvailRealX.description: The amount of real/physical memory currently unused or available.

memTotalFreeX.name: memTotalFreeX
memTotalFreeX.description: The total amount of memory free or available for use on this host. This value typically covers both real memory and swap space or virtual memory.

memMinimumSwapX.name: memMinimumSwapX
memMinimumSwapX.description: The minimum amount of swap space expected to be kept free or available during normal operation of this host. If this value (as reported by 'memAvailSwap(4)') falls below the specified level, then 'memSwapError(100)' will be set to 1 and an error message made available via 'memSwapErrorMsg(101)'.

memSharedX.name: memSharedX
memSharedX.description: The total amount of real or virtual memory currently allocated for use as shared memory. This object will not be implemented on hosts where the underlying operating system does not explicitly identify memory as specifically reserved for this purpose.

memBufferX.name: memBufferX
memBufferX.description: The total amount of real or virtual memory currently allocated for use as memory buffers. This object will not be implemented on hosts where the underlying operating system does not explicitly identify memory as specifically reserved for this purpose.

memCachedX.name: memCachedX
memCachedX.description: The total amount of real or virtual memory currently allocated for use as cached memory. This object will not be implemented on hosts where the underlying operating system does not explicitly identify memory as specifically reserved for this purpose.

memSwapError.name: memSwapError
memSwapError.description: Indicates whether the amount of available swap space (as reported by 'memAvailSwap(4)'), is less than the desired minimum (specified by 'memMinimumSwap(12)').

memSwapErrorMsg.name: memSwapErrorMsg
memSwapErrorMsg.description: Describes whether the amount of available swap space (as reported by 'memAvailSwap(4)'), is less than the desired minimum (specified by 'memMinimumSwap(12)').

dskTable.name: dskTable
dskTable.description: Disk watching information. Partions to be watched are configured by the snmpd.conf file of the agent.

dskEntry.name: dskEntry
dskEntry.description: An entry containing a disk and its statistics.

dskIndex.name: dskIndex
dskIndex.description: Integer reference number (row number) for the disk mib.

dskPath.name: dskPath
dskPath.description: Path where the disk is mounted.

dskDevice.name: dskDevice
dskDevice.description: Path of the device for the partition

dskMinimum.name: dskMinimum
dskMinimum.description: Minimum space required on the disk (in kBytes) before the errors are triggered. Either this or dskMinPercent is configured via the agent's snmpd.conf file.

dskMinPercent.name: dskMinPercent
dskMinPercent.description: Percentage of minimum space required on the disk before the errors are triggered. Either this or dskMinimum is configured via the agent's snmpd.conf file.

dskTotal.name: dskTotal
dskTotal.description: Total size of the disk/partion (kBytes). For large disks (>2Tb), this value will latch at INT32_MAX (2147483647).

dskAvail.name: dskAvail
dskAvail.description: Available space on the disk. For large lightly-used disks (>2Tb), this value will latch at INT32_MAX (2147483647).

dskUsed.name: dskUsed
dskUsed.description: Used space on the disk. For large heavily-used disks (>2Tb), this value will latch at INT32_MAX (2147483647).

dskPercent.name: dskPercent
dskPercent.description: Percentage of space used on disk

dskPercentNode.name: dskPercentNode
dskPercentNode.description: Percentage of inodes used on disk

dskTotalLow.name: dskTotalLow
dskTotalLow.description: Total size of the disk/partion (kBytes). Together with dskTotalHigh composes 64-bit number.

dskTotalHigh.name: dskTotalHigh
dskTotalHigh.description: Total size of the disk/partion (kBytes). Together with dskTotalLow composes 64-bit number.

dskAvailLow.name: dskAvailLow
dskAvailLow.description: Available space on the disk (kBytes). Together with dskAvailHigh composes 64-bit number.

dskAvailHigh.name: dskAvailHigh
dskAvailHigh.description: Available space on the disk (kBytes). Together with dskAvailLow composes 64-bit number.

dskUsedLow.name: dskUsedLow
dskUsedLow.description: Used space on the disk (kBytes). Together with dskUsedHigh composes 64-bit number.

dskUsedHigh.name: dskUsedHigh
dskUsedHigh.description: Used space on the disk (kBytes). Together with dskUsedLow composes 64-bit number.

dskErrorFlag.name: dskErrorFlag
dskErrorFlag.description: Error flag signaling that the disk or partition is under the minimum required space configured for it.

dskErrorMsg.name: dskErrorMsg
dskErrorMsg.description: A text description providing a warning and the space left on the disk.

laEntry.name: laEntry
laEntry.description: An entry containing a load average and its values.

laIndex.name: laIndex
laIndex.description: reference index/row number for each observed loadave.

laNames.name: laNames
laNames.description: The list of loadave names we're watching.

laLoad.name: laLoad
laLoad.description: The 1,5 and 15 minute load averages (one per row).

laConfig.name: laConfig
laConfig.description: The watch point for load-averages to signal an error. If the load averages rises above this value, the laErrorFlag below is set.

laLoadInt.name: laLoadInt
laLoadInt.description: The 1,5 and 15 minute load averages as an integer. This is computed by taking the floating point loadaverage value and multiplying by 100, then converting the value to an integer.

laLoadFloat.name: laLoadFloat
laLoadFloat.description: The 1,5 and 15 minute load averages as an opaquely wrapped floating point number.

laErrorFlag.name: laErrorFlag
laErrorFlag.description: A Error flag to indicate the load-average has crossed its threshold value defined in the snmpd.conf file. It is set to 1 if the threshold is crossed, 0 otherwise.

laErrMessage.name: laErrMessage
laErrMessage.description: An error message describing the load-average and its surpased watch-point value.

versionConfigureOptions.name: versionConfigureOptions
versionConfigureOptions.description: Options passed to the configure script when this agent was built.

versionClearCache.name: versionClearCache
versionClearCache.description: Set to 1 to clear the exec cache, if enabled

versionUpdateConfig.name: versionUpdateConfig
versionUpdateConfig.description: Set to 1 to read-read the config file(s).

versionRestartAgent.name: versionRestartAgent
versionRestartAgent.description: Set to 1 to restart the agent.

versionSavePersistentData.name: versionSavePersistentData
versionSavePersistentData.description: Set to 1 to force the agent to save it's persistent data immediately.

versionDoDebugging.name: versionDoDebugging
versionDoDebugging.description: Set to 1 to turn debugging statements on in the agent or 0 to turn it off.

snmperrErrorFlag.name: snmperrErrorFlag
snmperrErrorFlag.description: A Error flag to indicate trouble with the agent. It goes to 1 if there is an error, 0 if no error.

snmperrErrMessage.name: snmperrErrMessage
snmperrErrMessage.description: An error message describing the problem (if one exists).

mrTable.name: mrTable
mrTable.description: A table displaying all the oid's registered by mib modules in the agent. Since the agent is modular in nature, this lists each module's OID it is responsible for and the name of the module

mrEntry.name: mrEntry
mrEntry.description: An entry containing a registered mib oid.

mrIndex.name: mrIndex
mrIndex.description: The registry slot of a mibmodule.

mrModuleName.name: mrModuleName
mrModuleName.description: The module name that registered this OID.

ssIndex.name: ssIndex
ssIndex.description: Bogus Index. This should always return the integer 1.

ssErrorName.name: ssErrorName
ssErrorName.description: Bogus Name. This should always return the string 'systemStats'.

ssSwapIn.name: ssSwapIn
ssSwapIn.description: The average amount of memory swapped in from disk, calculated over the last minute.

ssSwapOut.name: ssSwapOut
ssSwapOut.description: The average amount of memory swapped out to disk, calculated over the last minute.

ssIOSent.name: ssIOSent
ssIOSent.description: The average amount of data written to disk or other block device, calculated over the last minute. This object has been deprecated in favour of 'ssIORawSent(57)', which can be used to calculate the same metric, but over any desired time period.

ssIOReceive.name: ssIOReceive
ssIOReceive.description: The average amount of data read from disk or other block device, calculated over the last minute. This object has been deprecated in favour of 'ssIORawReceived(58)', which can be used to calculate the same metric, but over any desired time period.

ssSysInterrupts.name: ssSysInterrupts
ssSysInterrupts.description: The average rate of interrupts processed (including the clock) calculated over the last minute. This object has been deprecated in favour of 'ssRawInterrupts(59)', which can be used to calculate the same metric, but over any desired time period.

ssSysContext.name: ssSysContext
ssSysContext.description: The average rate of context switches, calculated over the last minute. This object has been deprecated in favour of 'ssRawContext(60)', which can be used to calculate the same metric, but over any desired time period.

ssCpuUser.name: ssCpuUser
ssCpuUser.description: The percentage of CPU time spent processing user-level code, calculated over the last minute. This object has been deprecated in favour of 'ssCpuRawUser(50)', which can be used to calculate the same metric, but over any desired time period.

ssCpuSystem.name: ssCpuSystem
ssCpuSystem.description: The percentage of CPU time spent processing system-level code, calculated over the last minute. This object has been deprecated in favour of 'ssCpuRawSystem(52)', which can be used to calculate the same metric, but over any desired time period.

ssCpuIdle.name: ssCpuIdle
ssCpuIdle.description: The percentage of processor time spent idle, calculated over the last minute. This object has been deprecated in favour of 'ssCpuRawIdle(53)', which can be used to calculate the same metric, but over any desired time period.

ssCpuRawUser.name: ssCpuRawUser
ssCpuRawUser.description: The number of 'ticks' (typically 1/100s) spent processing user-level code. On a multi-processor system, the 'ssCpuRaw*' counters are cumulative over all CPUs, so their sum will typically be N*100 (for N processors).

ssCpuRawNice.name: ssCpuRawNice
ssCpuRawNice.description: The number of 'ticks' (typically 1/100s) spent processing reduced-priority code. This object will not be implemented on hosts where the underlying operating system does not measure this particular CPU metric. On a multi-processor system, the 'ssCpuRaw*' counters are cumulative over all CPUs, so their sum will typically be N*100 (for N processors).

ssCpuRawSystem.name: ssCpuRawSystem
ssCpuRawSystem.description: The number of 'ticks' (typically 1/100s) spent processing system-level code. On a multi-processor system, the 'ssCpuRaw*' counters are cumulative over all CPUs, so their sum will typically be N*100 (for N processors). This object may sometimes be implemented as the combination of the 'ssCpuRawWait(54)' and 'ssCpuRawKernel(55)' counters, so care must be taken when summing the overall raw counters.

ssCpuRawIdle.name: ssCpuRawIdle
ssCpuRawIdle.description: The number of 'ticks' (typically 1/100s) spent idle. On a multi-processor system, the 'ssCpuRaw*' counters are cumulative over all CPUs, so their sum will typically be N*100 (for N processors).

ssCpuRawWait.name: ssCpuRawWait
ssCpuRawWait.description: The number of 'ticks' (typically 1/100s) spent waiting for IO. This object will not be implemented on hosts where the underlying operating system does not measure this particular CPU metric. This time may also be included within the 'ssCpuRawSystem(52)' counter. On a multi-processor system, the 'ssCpuRaw*' counters are cumulative over all CPUs, so their sum will typically be N*100 (for N processors).

ssCpuRawKernel.name: ssCpuRawKernel
ssCpuRawKernel.description: The number of 'ticks' (typically 1/100s) spent processing kernel-level code. This object will not be implemented on hosts where the underlying operating system does not measure this particular CPU metric. This time may also be included within the 'ssCpuRawSystem(52)' counter. On a multi-processor system, the 'ssCpuRaw*' counters are cumulative over all CPUs, so their sum will typically be N*100 (for N processors).

ssCpuRawInterrupt.name: ssCpuRawInterrupt
ssCpuRawInterrupt.description: The number of 'ticks' (typically 1/100s) spent processing hardware interrupts. This object will not be implemented on hosts where the underlying operating system does not measure this particular CPU metric. On a multi-processor system, the 'ssCpuRaw*' counters are cumulative over all CPUs, so their sum will typically be N*100 (for N processors).

ssIORawSent.name: ssIORawSent
ssIORawSent.description: Number of blocks sent to a block device

ssIORawReceived.name: ssIORawReceived
ssIORawReceived.description: Number of blocks received from a block device

ssCpuRawSoftIRQ.name: ssCpuRawSoftIRQ
ssCpuRawSoftIRQ.description: The number of 'ticks' (typically 1/100s) spent processing software interrupts. This object will not be implemented on hosts where the underlying operating system does not measure this particular CPU metric. On a multi-processor system, the 'ssCpuRaw*' counters are cumulative over all CPUs, so their sum will typically be N*100 (for N processors).

ssCpuRawSteal.name: ssCpuRawSteal
ssCpuRawSteal.description: The number of 'ticks' (typically 1/100s) spent by the hypervisor code to run other VMs even though the CPU in the current VM had something runnable. This object will not be implemented on hosts where the underlying operating system does not measure this particular CPU metric. On a multi-processor system, the 'ssCpuRaw*' counters are cumulative over all CPUs, so their sum will typically be N*100 (for N processors).

ssCpuRawGuest.name: ssCpuRawGuest
ssCpuRawGuest.description: The number of 'ticks' (typically 1/100s) spent by the CPU to run a virtual CPU (guest). This object will not be implemented on hosts where the underlying operating system does not measure this particular CPU metric. On a multi-processor system, the 'ssCpuRaw*' counters are cumulative over all CPUs, so their sum will typically be N*100 (for N processors).

ssCpuRawGuestNice.name: ssCpuRawGuestNice
ssCpuRawGuestNice.description: The number of 'ticks' (typically 1/100s) spent by the CPU to run a niced virtual CPU (guest). This object will not be implemented on hosts where the underlying operating system does not measure this particular CPU metric. On a multi-processor system, the 'ssCpuRaw*' counters are cumulative over all CPUs, so their sum will typically be N*100 (for N processors).

ssCpuNumCpus.name: ssCpuNumCpus
ssCpuNumCpus.description: The number of processors, as counted by the agent. This object's value may be useful in the management of certain operating systems where notions such as load average do not take into account the number of processors in the system. For other objects in the systemStats group whose descriptions refer to 'N processors', this object's value is N.

ucdStart.name: ucdStart
ucdStart.description: This trap could in principle be sent when the agent start

ucdShutdown.name: ucdShutdown
ucdShutdown.description: This trap is sent when the agent terminates

logMatchMaxEntries.name: logMatchMaxEntries
logMatchMaxEntries.description: The maximum number of logmatch entries this snmpd daemon can support.

logMatchCurrentCounter.name: logMatchCurrentCounter
logMatchCurrentCounter.description: Regex match counter. This counter will be reset with each logfile rotation.

logMatchCounter.name: logMatchCounter
logMatchCounter.description: Regex match counter. This counter will be reset with each read

logMatchCycle.name: logMatchCycle
logMatchCycle.description: time between updates (if not queried) in seconds

logMatchErrorFlag.name: logMatchErrorFlag
logMatchErrorFlag.description: errorflag: is this line configured correctly?
